cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.DS 

This paper deals with interference management and multicasting in a wireless network, which are topics typically covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a joint design of coded caching and multicast beamforming, which falls under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the performance of the proposed scheme in terms of degrees-of-freedom, which is a concept related to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DS).
